read_int_arr = lambda : [int(x) for x in input().strip().split()]

def solve():
    (a, b) = read_int_arr()
    if a == b:
        print(-1)
        return
    n = abs(a - b)
    ans = 0
    i = 1
    while i * i <= n:
        if n % i == 0:
            ans += 1
            if i != n / i:
                ans += 1
        i += 1
    print(ans)
for _ in range(int(input())):
    solve()
